SIMPLE: nutrient
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nutrient
<hw>Nu"tri*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nutriens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>nutrire</ets>. See
<er>Nourish</er>.]</ety> <def>Nutritious; nourishing; promoting
growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nutrient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nutrient
<hw>Nu"tri*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Any substance which has nutritious qualities, <it>i.
e.</it>, which nourishes or promotes growth; a nutriment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Microbiology)</fld>
<def>A substance added to the growth medium of a microorganism to
promote growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nutrify</ent>⟦br⟧
